The paper proposes a method for medical image registration using a content adaptive mesh generation algorithm and a mesh-based discretization of the distance measure and regularization term. This involves techniques from computer vision (cs.CV) for image registration, information theory (cs.IT) for the energy functional, graphics (cs.GR) for mesh generation, multimedia (cs.MM) for spline interpolation, and numerical analysis (cs.NA) for solving the sparse system of linear equations. Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
